</div>

<div class="tp-caption WebProduct-Content   tp-resizeme  ch-header-text" id="slide-22-layer-5" data-x="['left','left','left','left']" data-hoffset="['34','34','26','26']" data-y="['top','top','top','top']" data-voffset="['182','182','301','301']" data-fontweight="['600','600','900','900']" data-width="['573','573','562','562']" data-height="['none','none','142','142']" data-whitespace="normal" data-transform_idle="o:1;" data-transform_in="opacity:0;s:300;e:Power2.easeInOut;" data-transform_out="opacity:0;s:300;s:300;" data-start="1200" data-splitin="none" data-splitout="none" data-responsive_offset="on" style="z-index: 6; min-width: 573px; max-width: 573px; white-space: normal; font-size: 24px; line-height: 28px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1.00);">Published by Hillsdale College Press, the official biography of Winston Churchill is the largest biography ever written. It was begun by Churchill's son, Randolph, expanded by the great historian Martin Gilbert, and is currently edited by Hillsdale College president Larry P. Arnn.
</div>

