<div class="tp-caption Fashion-BigDisplay   tp-resizeme  quote" id="slide-4-layer-1" data-x="['center','center','center','center']" data-hoffset="['0','0','0','0']" data-y="['middle','middle','middle','middle']" data-voffset="['-48','-48','-128','-128']" data-width="['1042','1042','773','773']" data-height="['none','none','181','181']" data-whitespace="normal" data-transform_idle="o:1;" data-transform_in="opacity:0;s:300;e:Power2.easeInOut;" data-transform_out="opacity:0;s:300;s:300;" data-start="500" data-splitin="none" data-splitout="none" data-responsive_offset="on" style="z-index: 5; min-width: 1042px; max-width: 1042px; white-space: normal; font-size: 34px; line-height: 36px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1.00);text-align:center;">“Still, I avow my hope and faith, sure and inviolate, that in the days to come the British and American peoples will for their own safety and for the good of all walk together side by side in majesty, in justice, and in peace.”
</div>

<div class="tp-caption Fashion-BigDisplay   tp-resizeme  quote-name" id="slide-4-layer-2" data-x="['center','center','center','center']" data-hoffset="['0','0','0','0']" data-y="['top','top','top','top']" data-voffset="['229','229','599','599']" data-width="594" data-height="61" data-whitespace="normal" data-transform_idle="o:1;" data-transform_in="opacity:0;s:300;e:Power2.easeInOut;" data-transform_out="opacity:0;s:300;s:300;" data-start="500" data-splitin="none" data-splitout="none" data-responsive_offset="on" style="z-index: 6; min-width: 594px; max-width: 594px; max-width: 61px; max-width: 61px; white-space: normal; font-size: 24px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1.00);text-align:center;">—U.S. Congress, Washington, 26 December 1941
</div>
</li>

