<div class="tp-caption Fashion-BigDisplay   tp-resizeme  quote" id="slide-5-layer-1" data-x="['center','center','center','center']" data-hoffset="['0','0','0','0']" data-y="['middle','middle','middle','middle']" data-voffset="['-48','-48','-138','-138']" data-width="['1042','1042','735','735']" data-height="none" data-whitespace="normal" data-transform_idle="o:1;" data-transform_in="opacity:0;s:300;e:Power2.easeInOut;" data-transform_out="opacity:0;s:300;s:300;" data-start="500" data-splitin="none" data-splitout="none" data-responsive_offset="on" style="z-index: 5; min-width: 1042px; max-width: 1042px; white-space: normal; font-size: 34px; line-height: 36px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1.00);text-align:center;">"There is not one single social or economic principle or concept in the philosophy of the Russian Bolshevik which has not been realized, carried into action, and enshrined in immutable laws a million years ago by the White Ant.”
</div>

<div class="tp-caption Fashion-BigDisplay   tp-resizeme  quote-name" id="slide-5-layer-2" data-x="['center','center','center','center']" data-hoffset="['0','0','0','0']" data-y="['top','top','top','top']" data-voffset="['229','229','658','658']" data-width="594" data-height="61" data-whitespace="normal" data-transform_idle="o:1;" data-transform_in="opacity:0;s:300;e:Power2.easeInOut;" data-transform_out="opacity:0;s:300;s:300;" data-start="500" data-splitin="none" data-splitout="none" data-responsive_offset="on" style="z-index: 6; min-width: 594px; max-width: 594px; max-width: 61px; max-width: 61px; white-space: normal; font-size: 24px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1.00);text-align:center;">—“Mass Effects in Modern Life,” July 1927
</div>
</li>

